ams\n| length13        = 5:08\n| title14         = Don't Hold Back\n| writer14        = {{hlist|Williams|Smith}}\n| length14        = 2:57\n| title15         = Beatbox\n| writer15        = {{hlist|Williams|Southey}}\n| length15        = 1:09\n| title16         = Encore\n| writer16        = Williams\n| length16        = 4:31\n| title17         = Destination\n| writer17        = {{hlist|Williams|Onallee|Watt|Thorn}}\n| length17        = 3:51\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\nAdapted from the liner notes.<ref>{{cite AV media notes|others=[[Roni Size & Reprazent]]|title=New Forms|year=1997|type=Liner Notes|publisher=[[Talkin' Loud]]}}</ref>\n{{Div col}}\n*[[Roni Size]] (Ryan Williams) \u2013 writing, production, keyboards\n*[[Onallee]] (Tracey Bowen) \u2013 vocals, writing\n*[[Dynamite MC]] (Dominic Smith) \u2013 vocals, writing\n*[[DJ Die]] (Daniel Kausman) \u2013 writing, production\n*DJ Suv (Paul Southey) \u2013 writing, production\n*[[Krust]] (Kirk Thompson) \u2013 writing, production\n*Clive Deemer \u2013 drums\n*Si John \u2013 bass\n*[[Bahamadia]] (Antonia Reed) \u2013 vocals\n*Tyrrell \u2013 guitar\n*Adrian Place \u2013 saxophone\n*[[Roisin Murphy]] - vocals (sampled)\n*Gilles Peterson \u2013 A&R\n*Paul Martin \u2013 A&R\n*Intro. London \u2013 design\n*Vikki Jackman \u2013 photography\n*Simon Goffe \u2013 management\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable unsortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Organisation\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"1\"| 1997\n| [[Mercury Prize]]\n| Mercury Album of the Year\n| {{Won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|.<br><ref>\n{{Cite web|title=It is Size that counts as Roni wins Mercury prize|website=[[The Independent]]|language=en|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/it-is-size-that-counts-as-roni-wins-mercury-prize-1247754.html|accessdate=5 July 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Chart (1997\u201398)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands ([[MegaCharts]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Roni Size - Reprazent - dutchcarts.nl|work=[[MegaCharts]]|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Roni+Size&titel=Reprazent+%2F+New+Forms&cat=a|accessdate=5 July 2019}}</ref>\n|96\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|New Zealand ([[Recorded Music NZ]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Charts.org.nz - Roni Size / Reprazent|work=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|url=https://charts.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Roni+Size&titel=Reprazent+%2F+New+Forms&cat=a|accessdate=5 July 2019}}</ref>\n|37\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[UK Albums Chart]] ([[Official Charts Company]])<ref name=\"occ\"/>\n|8\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US [[Heatseekers Albums]] (''[[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|title=Roni Size/Reprazent Chart History|work=[[Billboard charts]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/roni-size-reprazent/chart-history/heatseekers-albums|accessdate=5 July 2019}}</ref>\n|36\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=album|region=United Kingdom|artist=Roni Size/Reprazent|title=New Forms|award=Platinum|certyear=2013|relyear=1997}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Reprazent}}\n\n[[Category:1997 albums]]\n[[Category:Roni Size albums]]\n[[Category:Mercury Prize-winning albums]]\n[[Category:Talkin' Loud albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the sculpture by Tony Cragg|New Forms (sculpture)}}\n{{use British English|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = New Forms\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Roni Size & Reprazent]]\n| cover      =  New Forms album cover.png\n| alt        = \n| released   = {{Start date|df=yes|1997|06|23}}\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Drum and bass]]\n| length     = 139:54 \n| label      = {{hlist|[[Talkin' Loud]]|[[Mercury Records|Mercury]]|[[Universal Music Group|Universal]]}}\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Roni Size]]\n* [[DJ Die]]\n* [[Krust]]\n* DJ Suv\n}}\n| next_title = [[In the M\u00f8de]]\n| next_year  = 2000\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = New Forms\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Share the Fall\n | single1date = 19 May 1997\n | single2     = Heroes\n | single2date = 11 September 1997\n | single3     = Brown Paper Bag\n | single3date = 27 October 1997\n | single4     = Watching Windows\n | single4date = 28 April 1998\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''New Forms''''' is the debut studio album by British [[drum and bass]] group [[Roni Size & Reprazent]]. It was originally released on 23 June 1997 through [[Talkin' Loud]], and later re-released by [[Mercury Records]] and [[Universal Music Group]]. The album was released to critical and commercial success, winning the 1997 [[Mercury Prize]], [[platinum record|certifying platinum]] in the UK, and often being cited as their [[masterpiece|magnum opus]].<ref name=RAbiog>{{cite web|title=RA: Roni Size biography|url=http://www.residentadvisor.net/dj/ronisize/biography|publisher=[[Resident Advisor]]|accessdate=22 May 2013}}</ref>\n\n''New Forms'' was promoted by the release of its four singles, \"Share the Fall\", \"Heroes\", \"Brown Paper Bag\" and \"Watching Windows\", all landing on the [[UK Singles Chart]] and featuring vocals from [[Onallee]]. The album features production credits from [[Roni Size]], [[Krust]], [[DJ Die]] and Suv.\n\n==Release==\n''New Forms'' was preceded by a 1996 EP named ''Reasons for Sharing'' containing \"Share the Fall\", \"Down\", \"Trust Me\", and \"Sounds Fresh\", the former three of which were featured on the album.<ref>{{cite AV media notes|others=[[Roni Size & Reprazent]]|title=Reasons for Sharing|year=1996|type=Liner Notes|publisher=[[Talkin' Loud]]}}</ref> On 19 May 1997, the album's lead single was released, \"Share the Fall\", which reached number 37 in the [[UK Singles Chart]] in June that year. The album was released on 23 June 1997 and charted on the [[UK Albums Chart]] for 46 weeks, peaking at number 8. Following the album, three singles were released \"Heroes\", \"Brown Paper Bag\" and \"Watching Windows\", all charting at positions 31, 20 and 28 respectively, with \"Brown Paper Bag\" remaining the group's highest charting single.<ref name=\"occ\">{{cite web|title=Roni Size Reprazent - Full Official Chart History|work=[[Official Charts Company]]|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/6190/roni-size-reprazent/|accessdate=5 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe album was released in various formats, all with differing track lists. The original album release was a two disc CD, though single disc editions only containing disc one were later released.<ref>{{cite AV media notes|others=[[Roni Size & Reprazent]]|title=New Forms (Single Disc)|year=1997|type=Liner Notes|publisher=[[Talkin' Loud]]}} 534 934-2</ref> The cassette  version comprised the first disc of the CD.<ref>{{cite AV media notes|others=[[Roni Size & Reprazent]]|title=New Forms (Cassette)|year=1997|type=Liner Notes|publisher=[[Talkin' Loud]]}} 534 933-4</ref> Two vinyl versions were released, a 5x and 4x LP. Of the two vinyl versions, the most common pressing is the 4LP version comprising most of the first CD; the 5x LP set includes tracks from the second CD, replacing \"Intro\" with \"Heroes\" and \"Digital\", which are appended to the end.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Roni-Size-Reprazent-New-Forms/release/68733|title=Roni Size / Reprazent \u2013 New Forms (5x12\", Album) at Discogs}}</ref> In the US, only the 2CD version was released, which contained the bonus track \"Electricks\". \n\nIn 2008, a remake of the original album, ''New Forms\u00b2'', was released in April 2008. Roni Size has described it as having a \"new coat of armour added to the original tracks\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bandweblogs.com/blog/2008/03/25/roni-sizereprazent-new-forms-2-release-dont-hold-back-single/ |title=Roni Size/Reprazent: New Forms 2 release + \"Don\u2019t Hold Back\" single |publisher=Band Weblogs |date=25 March 2008 |accessdate=3 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120214145253/http://bandweblogs.com/blog/2008/03/25/roni-sizereprazent-new-forms-2-release-dont-hold-back-single/ |archivedate=14 February 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The album contains four new songs: \"Heart to Heart\", \"Less is More\", \"Don't Hold Back\" and \"Encore\", while omitting several of the songs from the original album.\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album reviews\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref name=allmusic>{{cite web|last=Bush|first=John|title=New Forms \u2013 Roni Size / Roni Size & Reprazent|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/new-forms-mw0000028036|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=22 May 2013}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| rev2score = A<ref name=\"ew\">{{cite journal|last=Sakharow|first=Anya|title=New Forms|url=https://www.ew.com/article/1997/10/31/album-review-new-forms|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=31 October 1997|accessdate=14 June 2016}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite news|last=Bennun|first=David|title=Roni Size: New Forms (Talkin' Loud)|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=4 July 1997}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''\n| rev4score = {{Rating|3|4}}<ref>{{cite news|last=Hochman|first=Steve|title=Roni Size/Reprazent, 'New Forms,' Talkin' Loud/Mercury|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1997/nov/23/entertainment/ca-56717|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=23 November 1997|accessdate=14 June 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160810181133/http://articles.latimes.com/1997/nov/23/entertainment/ca-56717|archivedate=10 August 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[Muzik]]''\n| rev5score = 10/10<ref>{{cite journal|last=Newsome|first=Rachel|title=Reprazent Featuring Roni Size: New Forms (Talkin' Loud)|work=[[Muzik]]|issue=26|date=July 1997|page=119}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev6score = 9/10<ref>{{cite journal|last=Newsome|first=Rachel|title=Roni Size/Reprazent \u2013 New Forms|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews/19980101000933reviews.html|work=[[NME]]|accessdate=14 June 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000817183405/http://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews/19980101000933reviews.html|archivedate=17 August 2000|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev7score = 7.7/10<ref name=p4k>{{cite web|last=Schreiber|first=Ryan|title=Roni Size: New Forms [with Reprazent]|url=http://www.pitchforkmedia.com/article/record_review/21770-new-forms-with-reprazent|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=1 November 1997|accessdate=18 June 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514120233/http://www.pitchforkmedia.com/article/record_review/21770-new-forms-with-reprazent|archivedate=14 May 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]''\n| rev8score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite journal|last=Howe|first=Rupert|title=Roni Size/Reprazent: New Forms|work=[[Q (magazine)|Q]]|issue=379|date=December 2017|page=115}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev9score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite journal|last=Fricke|first=David|authorlink=David Fricke|title=Roni Size and Reprazent: New Forms|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/artists/ronisizeandreprazent/albums/album/220084/review/5940519/new_forms|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=16 December 1997|accessdate=14 June 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080605235529/http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/ronisizeandreprazent/albums/album/220084/review/5940519/new_forms|archivedate=5 June 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]''\n| rev10score = 8/10<ref name=\"spin\">{{cite journal|last=Reynolds|first=Simon|authorlink=Simon Reynolds|title=RoniSize/Reprazent: New Forms|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZsS_O9LQNKAC&pg=PA153|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|volume=13|issue=9|date=December 1997|accessdate=6 June 2013|page=153|issn=0886-3032}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''New Forms'' was released to favourable reviews. [[AllMusic]] described the album as \"the major statement on drum'n'bass\", rating it five stars out of five,<ref name=allmusic/> while in 2010 [[BBC Music]] noted that it \"carved a mainstream niche for drum and bass like no album before it\".<ref name=bbc>{{cite web|last=Diver|first=Mike|title=BBC \u2013 Music \u2013 Review of Roni Size & Reprazent \u2013 New Forms|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/jh6m|publisher=[[BBC Music]]|date=25 October 2010|accessdate=22 May 2013}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' noted the album's \"caffeinated drum beat and blissful bass reverb\".<ref name=\"ew\"/> ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'}}s Ryan Schreiber was less generous, commenting that the album \"doesn't really get decent until the second half of disc one\".<ref name=p4k/>\n\n==Track listing==\nThe original CD release contains both discs, though a single disc version containing only disc 1 was additionally released in the UK.\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Disc 1 / Cassette\n| title1          = Railing\n| writer1         = {{hlist|[[Roni Size|Ryan Williams]]|[[Dynamite MC|Dominic Smith]]}}\n| length1         = 2:05\n| title2          = Brown Paper Bag\n| length2         = 9:03\n| writer2         = Williams\n| title3          = New Forms\n| note3           = featuring [[Bahamadia]]\n| writer3         = {{hlist|Williams|[[Bahamadia|Antonia Reed]]|Paul Southey}}\n| length3         = 7:45\n| title4          = Let's Get It On\n| length4         = 6:57\n| writer4         = Williams\n| title5          = Digital\n| writer5         = {{hlist|Williams|[[Onallee]]}}\n| length5         = 9:05\n| title6          = Matter of Fact\n| writer6         = Williams\n| length6         = 4:05\n| title7          = Mad Cat\n| writer7         = Williams\n| length7         = 4:56\n| title8          = Heroes\n| writer8         = {{hlist|Williams|Onallee}}\n| length8         = 6:35\n| title9          = Share the Fall