 \n|'''12'''\n|6\n|4\n|3\n|6\n|2\n|6\n|3\n|10\n|10\n|10\n|6|| 119\n|-\n|12\n| align=\"left\" | \"Vida minha\" ||'''12'''||'''12'''||'''12'''||'''12'''|| 4\n|'''12'''\n|2\n|'''12'''\n|5\n|'''12'''\n|'''12'''\n|7\n|10\n|'''12'''\n|'''12'''\n|5\n|8\n|'''12'''\n|'''12'''\n|'''12'''|| 197\n|}\n==At Eurovision==\nPortugal competed 6th in the second semi-final on 24 May.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hondal|first=Victor|title=Insignia exchange and semifinal allocation draw.|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/18162|publisher=EscToday.com}}</ref> After the voting, Filipa Sousa finished in 13th position with 39 points, which meant that for the second year in a row Portugal did not qualify for the final.\n\n===Points awarded by Portugal<ref>[[Eurovision Song Contest 2012]]</ref>===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Semi-final 2====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|width=20% bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''12 points'''||{{Esc|EST}}\n|-\n|width=20% bgcolor=\"silver\"|'''10 points'''||{{Esc|SWE}}\n|-\n|width=20% bgcolor=\"#CC9966\"|'''8 points'''||{{Esc|SRB}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''7 points'''||{{Esc|LIT}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''6 points'''||{{Esc|BUL}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''5 points'''||{{Esc|BIH}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''4 points'''||{{Esc|SVK}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''3 points'''||{{Esc|NOR}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''2 points'''||{{Esc|UKR}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''1 point'''||{{Esc|GEO}}\n|-\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Final====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|width=20% bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''12 points'''||{{Esc|ESP}}\n|-\n|width=20% bgcolor=\"silver\"|'''10 points'''||{{Esc|GER}}\n|-\n|width=20% bgcolor=\"#CC9966\"|'''8 points'''||{{Esc|RUS}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''7 points'''||{{Esc|EST}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''6 points'''||{{Esc|MDA}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''5 points'''||{{Esc|SRB}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''4 points'''||{{Esc|ROM}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''3 points'''||{{Esc|SWE}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''2 points'''||{{Esc|ITA}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''1 point'''||{{Esc|UKR}}\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Jury points awarded by Portugal===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Semi-final 2====\nJury points awarded in second semi-final:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|width=20%|'''12 points'''||{{Esc|Estonia}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''10 points'''||{{Esc|Serbia}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''8 points'''||{{Esc|Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''7 points'''||{{Esc|Slovakia}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''6 points'''||{{Esc|Sweden}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''5 points'''||{{Esc|Georgia}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''4 points'''||{{Esc|Croatia}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''3 points'''||{{Esc|Malta}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''2 points'''||{{Esc|Belarus}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''1 point'''||{{Esc|Slovenia}}\n|-\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Final====\nJury points awarded in the final:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|width=20%|'''12 points'''||{{Esc|Spain}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''10 points'''||{{Esc|Germany}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''8 points'''||{{Esc|Estonia}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''7 points'''||{{Esc|Serbia}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''6 points'''||{{Esc|Italy}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''5 points'''||{{Esc|Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''4 points'''||{{Esc|France}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''3 points'''||{{Esc|Albania}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''2 points'''||{{Esc|Iceland}}\n|-\n|width=20%|'''1 point'''||{{Esc|Russia}}\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|+Points awarded to Portugal (semi-final 2)\n|-\n!width=20%|12 points\n!width=20%|10 points\n!width=20%|8 points\n!width=20%|7 points\n!width=20%|6 points\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{esc|FRA}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{esc|NED}}\n|-\n!width=20%|5 points\n!width=20%|4 points\n!width=20%|3 points\n!width=20%|2 points\n!width=20%|1 point\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{esc|NOR}}\n*{{esc|SVK}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{esc|BIH}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{esc|CRO}}\n*{{esc|GER}}\n*{{esc|SLO}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{esc|LIT}}\n*{{esc|TUR}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{in lang|pt}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20120122001345/http://ww1.rtp.pt/icmblogs/rtp/comunicacao/?k=Regulamento-Festival-da-Cancao-2012---RTP.rtp&post=37042 Competition rules] ''[[R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal|RTP]]''\n\n{{Portugal in the Eurovision Song Contest}}\n{{Eurovision Song Contest 2012}}\n\n[[Category:Countries in the Eurovision Song Contest 2012]]\n[[Category:Portugal in the Eurovision Song Contest]]\n[[Category:2012 in Portugal]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toSantar\u00e9m(link changed toSantar\u00e9m, Portugal) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portugal_in_the_Eurovision_Song_Contest_2012"}
{"title_page": "Portugal in the Eurovision Song Contest 2011", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{short description|Portugal in the Eurovision Song Contest}}\n{{Infobox song contest national year\n| Year                   = 2011\n| Country                = Portugal\n| Preselection           = Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o 2011\n| Preselection date      = '''Online vote'''<br>20&ndash;27 January 2011<br>'''Final'''<br>5 March 2011\n| Entrant                = [[Homens da Luta]]\n| Song                   = [[A luta \u00e9 alegria]]\n| SF result              = ''Failed to qualify'' (18th, 22 points)\n| Final result           =\n}}\n'''Portugal''' participated in the '''Eurovision Song Contest 2011''' in [[D\u00fcsseldorf]], [[Germany]], having selected their entry through a televised national final, organised by Portuguese broadcaster [[R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal]] (RTP).\n\n==Before Eurovision==\n\n=== Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o 2011 ===\n''Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o 2011'' was the 47th edition of [[Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o]], the music competition that selects Portugal's entries for the Eurovision Song Contest.\n\n==== Format ====\nThe competition featured twenty-four songs. All twenty-four songs first faced an online vote held between 20 and 27 January 2011 where the top twelve songs advanced to the final. In the final, held on 5 March 2011, the winner was determined by a combination of the votes from 20 regional juries (50%) and televoting (50%).\n\n==== Competing entries ====\nArtists and songwriters were able to submit their song entries until 16 January 2011. Songwriters of any nationality were allowed to submit entries, but songs were required to be performed by citizens of Portugal and in the [[Portuguese language]].<ref name=\"Portugal3\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=9091|title=PORTUGAL - Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o back in 2011|last=Costa|first=Nelson|date=2010-11-05|publisher=Oikotimes.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111228075014/http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=9091|archivedate=2011-12-28|accessdate=2010-11-05}}</ref><ref name=\"Portugal4\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=9108|title=PORTUGAL - Portugal decides on March 5|last=Costa|first=Nelson|date=2010-11-08|publisher=Oikotimes.com|accessdate=2010-11-08}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref> From all submissions received, a selection committee chose twenty-four entries for the online voting.\n\n====Online voting====\nAfter the twenty-four competing entries were announced, an online public vote ran from 20 January 2011 until 27 January 2011, enabling users to vote for their favorite entries each day.<ref name=\"onlineresults\">{{cite news|author=RTP|url=http://ww1.rtp.pt/tvonline/sites/festival_cancao2011/?k=12-CANCOES-APURADAS-PARA-O-FC2011.rtp&post=2113|title=12 CAN\u00c7\u00d5ES APURADAS PARA O FC2011|date=2011-01-28|accessdate=2011-01-28|publisher=[[R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal|RTP]]|author-link=R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal}}{{dead link|date=March 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref> The twelve entries with the most votes advanced to the final of [[Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o]] 2011.<ref name=\"Portugal1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/16244|title=Portugal: RTP announces Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o 2011|last=Hondal|first=Victor|date=2010-11-19|publisher=EscToday.com|accessdate=2010-11-19}}</ref><ref name=\"Portugal2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=9236|title=Submissions begins today in Portugal|last=Costa|first=Nelson|date=2010-11-19|website=www.oikotimes.com|accessdate=2010-11-19}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"margin: 1em auto 1em auto\"\n! colspan=\"5\" |Online vote \u2013 20 January 2011 \u2013 27 January 2011\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\"\n! Artist\n! Song\n! Lyrics (l) / Music (m)\n! Votes\n! Place\n|- bgcolor=\"navajowhite\"\n|'''[[Homens da Luta]]'''||'''\"[[A luta \u00e9 alegria]]\"'''||'''Vasco Duarte (m), Jel (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''17,374'''|| align=\"center\" |'''1'''\n|-\n| Alma Real || \"N\u00e3o quero Falar\" || Thorsten Rath (m), S\u00e9rgio de Oliveira (l) || align=\"center\" | 12,431 || align=\"center\" | 13\n|- bgcolor=\"#F08080\"\n| Miguel Gizzas || \"Amor Cruzado\" || Miguel Gizzas (m & l) || align=\"center\" |\u2014\n| align=\"center\" |\u2014<ref name=\"ww1.rtp.pt\">{{cite web|url=http://ww1.rtp.pt/tvonline/sites/festival_cancao2011/?k=Comunicado-n-1.rtp&post=2081|title=Archived copy|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110125202023/http://ww1.rtp.pt/tvonline/sites/festival_cancao2011/?k=Comunicado-n-1.rtp&post=2081|archivedate=2011-01-25|accessdate=2011-01-21}}</ref>\n|- bgcolor=\"#F08080\"\n| Ant\u00f3nio Jos\u00e9 Silva || \"Por Ti\" || Ant\u00f3nio Jos\u00e9 Silva (m & l) || align=\"center\" |\u2014\n| align=\"center\" |\u2014<ref name=\"ww1.rtp.pt\" />\n|- bgcolor=\"#F08080\"\n| Bettershell || \"Um Sinal\" || Bettershell (m), Isa\u00edas Ricardo de Oliveira (l) || align=\"center\" |\u2014\n| align=\"center\" |\u2014<ref name=\"ww1.rtp.pt\" />\n|-\n| Sandra D\u00f3ria || \"Aprende a Voar (nas asas do amor)\" || Lu\u00eds Filipe Aguilar (m & l) || align=\"center\" | 2,470 || align=\"center\" | 18\n|-\n| Woodu || \"O Tempo Resolve Tudo\" || Bem Talbot (m), [[Jos\u00e9 Cid]] (m), Ana Sofia Cid (l) || align=\"center\" | 261 || align=\"center\" | 21\n|-\n| Emanuel Santos || \"N\u00e3o estamos s\u00f3s\" ||[[Ralph Siegel]] (m), [[Bernd Meinunger]] (m), Pedro Coelho (l) || align=\"center\" | 694 || align=\"center\" | 20\n|-\n| N\u00e1dia Correia || \"Sonhos do Verbo Amar\" || Ricardo Verdelho (m & l) || align=\"center\" | 11,651 || align=\"center\" | 15\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''Henrique Feist'''||'''\"Quase a Voar\"'''||'''Nuno Feist (m), Jos\u00e9 Fanha (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''13,844'''|| align=\"center\" |'''8'''\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''Wanda Stuart'''||'''\"Chegar \u00e0 tua voz\"'''||'''Paul Teixeira da Sousa (m & l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''14,394'''|| align=\"center\" |'''2'''\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''T\u00e2nia Tavares'''||'''\"Se esse Dia Chegar\"'''||'''[[Georgios kalpakidis|Gorgi]] (m), T\u00e2nia Tavares, (l) Nuno Val\u00e9rio (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''13,592'''|| align=\"center\" |'''11'''\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''Rui Andrade'''||'''\"Em Nome do Amor\"'''||'''Artur Guimar\u00e3es (m), Carlos Meireles (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''13,656'''|| align=\"center\" |'''10'''\n|-\n| Carla Ribeiro || \"S\u00f3 Acontece uma Vez\" || Jo\u00e3o Sanguilheira (m), Jo\u00e3o Novo (l) || align=\"center\" | 4,862 || align=\"center\" | 17\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''In\u00eas Bernardo'''||'''\"Deixa o Meu Lugar\"'''||'''Leonel Monteiro (m), Joana Ferraz (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''14,105'''|| align=\"center\" |'''3'''\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''Axel'''||'''\"Boom Boom Yeah\"'''||'''Jos\u00e9 F\u00e9lix (m), Axel (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''13,448'''|| align=\"center\" |'''12'''\n|-\n| Carla Pires || \"Voar Alto\" || Artur Guimar\u00e3es (m), Paulo Pires de Lima (l) || align=\"center\" | 11,967 || align=\"center\" | 14\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''7Saias'''||'''\"Embalo do Cora\u00e7\u00e3o\"'''||'''P\u00e1quito C. Braziel (m), Ana Rita Rebello (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''14,056'''|| align=\"center\" |'''6'''\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''Carla Moreno'''||'''\"Sobrevivo\"'''||'''[[Andrej Babi\u0107]] (m), Carlos Coelho (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''13,868'''|| align=\"center\" |'''7'''\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''Filipa Ruas'''||'''\"Tens\u00e3o\"'''||'''Daniel Nilsson (m), [[Henrik Szabo]] (m), Johnny Sanchez (m), [[Jonas Gladnikoff]] (m), Mike Eriksson (m), Filipa Ruas (l), Pedro S\u00e1 (l)'''\n| align=\"center\" |'''14,058'''|| align=\"center\" |'''5'''\n|-\n| Daniela Galbin || \"Amor A S\u00e9rio\" || Pedro Saraiva (m), Daniela Galbin (l) || align=\"center\" | 829 || align=\"center\" | 19\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''Nuno Norte'''||'''\"S\u00e3o os Barcos de Lisboa\"'''||'''Carlos Massa (m & l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''13,817'''|| align=\"center\" |'''9'''\n|-\n| Pop Pin's || \"Esta Noite Vamos Curtir\" || Jos\u00e9 Cardoso (m), Guy Ribeiro (l) || align=\"center\" | 7,325 || align=\"center\" | 16\n|- bgcolor=\" #FFDEAD\"\n|'''Ricardo Sousa'''||'''\"O mar, o vento, e as estrelas\"'''||'''Carlos Freitas (m), Fernando Guerreiro (l)'''|| align=\"center\" |'''14,062'''|| align=\"center\" |'''4'''\n|}\n\n====Final====\nThe final was held on 5 March 2011 at the [[Teatro Cam\u00f5es]] in [[Lisbon]], hosted by [[S\u00edlvia Alberto]] and Joana Teles ([[green room]] host). The 12 qualifying artists from the online voting held in January 2011 competed during the show, and the winner was determined by a combination of the votes from 20 regional juries (50%) and televoting (50%).<ref name=\"Portugal5\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=9727|title=RTP confirms the 12 finalists|last=Costa|first=Nelson|date=2011-01-28|publisher=Oikotimes.com|accessdate=2011-01-28}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref><ref name=\"Portugal6\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=9796|title=RTP announce Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o final running order|last=Costa|first=Nelson|date=2011-02-01|publisher=Oikotimes.com|accessdate=2011-02-01}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"margin: 1em auto 1em auto; text-align:center\"\n! colspan=\"9\" |Final \u2013 5 March 2011\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Draw\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Artist\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Song\n! colspan=\"2\" |Jury\n! colspan=\"2\" |Televote\n! r